ZH: 妈妈正在剪剪我的头发。
EN: Mom is cutting my hair.

ZH: 我买了一把剪，可以剪纸。
EN: I bought a pair of scissors to cut paper.

ZH: 羊毛剪起来很困难。
EN: It is difficult to shear wool.

ZH: 她在剪花布，准备缝制衣服。
EN: She is cutting flower-patterned fabric to make clothes.

ZH: 这把剪很锋利，小心使用。
EN: This pair of scissors is very sharp, be careful when using it.

ZH: 剪羊毛是一个耗时的工作。
EN: Shearing sheep takes a lot of time.

ZH: 我喜欢剪报纸，可以做成一些手工作品。
EN: I like cutting newspapers to make some handicrafts.

ZH: 奶奶每天都会剪几束花放在花瓶里。
EN: Grandma cuts a few flowers every day and puts them in a vase.

ZH: 剪衣服的尺寸一定要准确，否则就会影响穿着。
EN: The size of the cut clothes must be accurate, otherwise it will affect the fit.

ZH: 剪剪头发可以换个新形象。
EN: Cutting hair can give you a new look.

ZH: 她在剪羊毛时手很熟练。
EN: She is very skilled at shearing sheep.

ZH: 这把大剪刀很适合用来剪草。
EN: This large pair of scissors is suitable for cutting grass.

ZH: 剪牡丹花时要小心，不要伤到手指。
EN: Be careful when cutting peonies so as not to hurt your fingers.

ZH: 他剪完头发后看起来年轻了好多。
EN: He looks much younger after cutting his hair.

ZH: 剪头发后，她变得更加自信了。
EN: She became more confident after cutting her hair.

ZH: 剪羊毛是一门技术活。
EN: Shearing sheep is a skilled job.

ZH: 剪羊毛时要保持手稳定。
EN: Keep your hand steady when shearing sheep.

ZH: 剪羊毛是一项传统技艺。
EN: Shearing sheep is a traditional skill.

ZH: 手工剪剪花草，是一种很好的休闲方式。
EN: Hand-cutting flowers and plants is a good leisure activity.

ZH: 剪羊毛时要小心不要剪到肉。
EN: Be careful not to cut the flesh when shearing sheep.
